[2] Why do people without money make such thoughtless choices? Former British President Margaret Thatcher said, "Poverty is a character flaw." This is obvious, but there are those who say that it is a character flaw and that it is their own fault, and those who say that they should be helped. A survey of sugarcane farmers revealed that poverty leads to a significantly lower IQ than normal. In a word, poverty is the "psychology of scarcity." And it doesn't matter what they are lacking. If there are many things lacking, there is more to do. And errors occur. In modern times, these poor people are dealt with in a cheap way. He thought that it would be better to change the circumstances of the poor. It is a simple idea of "basic income guarantee" from the past. This not only made people wealthy, but also healthy. And it is much cheaper than the subsidies that are being spent on poverty measures. I feel that this could be a solution to all the problems that are happening now.
[3] Poor people have more debt, less savings, smoke more, don't exercise, drink more alcohol, and have poor eating habits. American psychologists administered intelligence tests to sugarcane farmers in India before and after harvest. It was found that the performance before the harvest period was lower than after the harvest period. Poor people are in a state of exhaustion because they have too much to do. Therefore, he thought that money should be given to poor people like increasing computer memory. The Canadian town of Dauphin actually gave away money to the poor and reduced poverty to zero. In addition to solving poverty, it has also improved children's performance and health. A basic income guarantee is more meaningful than just a policy. You can also change the concept of work. Inequality is caused by a lack of money. That's why he said there should be a basic income guarantee.
